.TH "HPC\-COMPOSE\-REACH" "1" "" "hpc\-compose 0.1.48" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hpc\-compose\-reach \- Print the SSH tunnel to reach a tracked service from a laptop
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
hpc\-compose reach [OPTIONS] <SERVICE>
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Resolve the SSH port\-forward needed to reach a tracked service's TCP/HTTP readiness port from a laptop: the compute node comes from tracked status and the port from the service readiness. Prints the `ssh \-L` command (with connection multiplexing so an OTP login node prompts only once), or runs it in the foreground with \-\-open. Read\-only; never daemonizes a tunnel.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fISERVICE\fR
Service whose readiness port should be forwarded.
.TP
\fB-f\fR, \fB--file\fR \fIFILE\fR
Compose specification file to read; if omitted, use the active context compose file or fall back to compose.yaml.
.TP
\fB--job\-id\fR \fIJOB_ID\fR
Tracked Slurm job id to reach instead of the latest recorded submission.
.TP
\fB--port\fR \fIPORT\fR
Override the forwarded port; required for services without TCP/HTTP readiness.
.TP
\fB--open\fR
Run the port\-forward in the foreground (Ctrl\-C to stop) instead of printing the command.
.TP
\fB--format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR
Output format. Possible values: text, json.
.TP
\fB--squeue\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the squeue executable. Default: squeue.
.TP
\fB--sacct\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the sacct executable. Default: sacct.
.TP
\fB--color\fR \fIWHEN\fR
Controls colored output. Default: auto. Possible values: auto, always, never.
.TP
\fB--quiet\fR
Suppress progress indicators and non\-essential labels.
.TP
\fB--profile\fR \fINAME\fR
Profile name to load from .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB--settings\-file\fR \fIPATH\fR
Explicit settings file path; defaults to upward search for .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Print help (see a summary with '\-h').
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
